SENATOR JOHN KENNEDY: ... I think our generation of Americans has the same rendezvous. The question now is: Can freedom be maintained under the most severe tack – attack it has ever known? I think it can be. And I think in the final analysis it depends upon what we do here. I think it’s time America started moving again.
SMITH: And now the opening statement by Vice President Richard M. Nixon.
